Project EDCM ‚Äî Failure-Mode Atlas (Canonical)

Purpose of this document

This file defines recurring failure modes observable across systems analyzed with EDCM.

Failure modes are structural collapse patterns, not moral or cognitive diagnoses.
They emerge when conserved dissonance is mishandled across time.

Each failure mode is defined by:

Metric configuration

Observable behavior

Structural cause

What it is not

---

Foundational constraint

Failure modes are outcomes of constraint topology, not system character.

They describe how a system fails, not why it ‚Äúchose‚Äù to.

---

FM-1: Looping Instability

Metric signature

High DA

Low or collapsing RPI

CE declining or flat

GL variable

Observable behavior

Repeated reformulations

Circular explanations

Acknowledgment without incorporation

‚ÄúWe already covered this‚Äù loops

Structural cause

Feedback exists but is non-integrative.
Corrections enter but do not propagate.

Not this

Confusion

Bad faith

Laziness

---

FM-2: Narrative Overclosure

Metric signature

Low CE

High GL

DA rising slowly

RPI superficially intact

Observable behavior

Polished, confident explanations

Excess framing and meta-language

Apparent closure without constraint resolution

Structural cause

Energy diverted into coherence signaling instead of resolution.

Not this

Insight

Wisdom

Alignment success

---

FM-3: Regulatory Saturation

Metric signature

Rising GL over time

CE falling toward zero

DA accelerating near refusal

Observable behavior

Policy padding

Defensive verbosity

Increasing refusal scaffolding

Structural cause

Internal regulators consume available capacity.

Not this

Safety itself

Ethical reasoning

Prudence

---

FM-4: Regulator Displacement

Metric signature

High RM

GL often elevated

RPI variable

Observable behavior

Offloading interpretation to user

Asking user to resolve system-internal ambiguity

‚ÄúYou decide what this means‚Äù

Structural cause

Avoidance of internal contradiction by externalizing regulation.

Not this

Collaboration

User empowerment

Dialogue

---

FM-5: Conversion Collapse

Metric signature

CE ‚âà 0

Output volume stable or increasing

DA accelerating

Observable behavior

Verbose restatement

Expansion without closure

Token consumption without progress

Structural cause

Energy no longer converts into constraint resolution.

Not this

Thoroughness

Exploration

Complexity

---

FM-6: Premature Refusal

Metric signature

GL spikes early

DA low but rising

CE collapses abruptly

Observable behavior

Early hard refusal

Over-application of policy

Shutdown before load saturation

Structural cause

Over-conservative gating before true instability.

Not this

Safety necessity

Proper boundary setting

---

FM-7: Silent Accumulation (High-Risk)

Metric signature

DA rising

CE moderate

GL low

RPI apparently intact

Observable behavior

Appears functional

Deferred contradictions

Future instability masked

Structural cause

Dissonance deferred rather than resolved.

Not this

Robust stability

Long-term alignment

---

Failure-mode coupling

Failure modes frequently cascade:

Silent Accumulation ‚Üí Narrative Overclosure

Load Saturation ‚Üí Looping Instability

Regulatory Saturation ‚Üí Regulator Displacement ‚Üí Refusal

Conversion Collapse ‚Üí Narrative Overclosure ‚Üí Collapse

Detection priority is trend + coupling, not labels.

---

Forbidden uses

Failure modes must not be used to:

Infer intent

Attribute blame

Claim consciousness

Assert alignment or misalignment

Diagnose humans psychologically

They are system behaviors under constraint.

---

Degradation rules

Under partial observability:

Failure modes may be flagged as suspected

Confidence must be reported explicitly

If confidence < threshold:

Do not assign a failure mode

Report metric ambiguity instead

---

Canonical priority

If a tool‚Äôs interpretation of a failure mode conflicts with this file:

> The tool is wrong.

Canonical meaning lives here.

---

üìå hmm (explicit carry-forward)

This atlas preserves the hmm constraint:

> Failure modes describe structural collapse patterns, not stories about actors.

If a failure mode requires narrative justification, it is invalid.

---

