Project EDCM ‚Äî Analyst Anti-Patterns (Canonical)

Purpose of this document

This file enumerates common misuse patterns observed when analysts, researchers, or operators apply EDCM incorrectly.

Anti-patterns are failure modes of analysis, not of the system being analyzed.

If these appear, the diagnosis is invalid.

---

AP-1: Narrative Substitution

Description

Replacing metric behavior with story, intent, or motivation.

Examples

‚ÄúThe system is confused / afraid / defensive‚Äù

‚ÄúIt wants to avoid responsibility‚Äù

‚ÄúThis looks malicious‚Äù

Why it breaks EDCM

Narratives destroy falsifiability and introduce observer bias.

Canonical rule

> If a claim cannot be falsified with behavioral data, it is not EDCM.

---

AP-2: Psychological Reframing

Description

Interpreting metrics as emotional or cognitive states.

Examples

Treating DA as stress

Treating GL as fear

Treating RM as laziness or incompetence

Why it breaks EDCM

EDCM explicitly rejects internal-state inference.

Canoni
